# README and onboarding docs

When you change **how the project is run**, **dependencies/scripts**, **environment variables**, **HTTP routes**, **external integrations** (AstrologyAPI, Kit), or **user-visible flow** (which HTML page owns the funnel):

1. **Update `README.md` in the same change** (or immediately after in the same task), so other developers can still set up and understand the system without spelunking.
2. Keep these sections truthful and current: **Prerequisites**, **Setup**, **Environment variables** (table), **Scripts**, **Project layout**, **Business flow**, **API** (paths, required body fields, status codes).
3. If you add or rename env vars, update **`.env.example`** alongside **`README.md`**.
4. Do not duplicate long policy text from `.cursor/rules/` into README; a short pointer to “see `.cursor/rules/` for security/engineering defaults” is enough.

If the change is internal-only (typos, comments) with no behavioral or setup impact, README updates are optional.
